topic.title: Supported BMP Mappings

body.p: MAPOTN supports up to 600G bandwidth with maximum 60 channels for BMP and IMP mapping, and up to 600G bandwidth with maximum 6 channels for BGMP. Table 1, Table 2 and Table 3 lists BMP, BGMP and IMP mappings supported by MAPOTN.

entry.p: ODUflex <-> MAPOTN [BMP:Nominal,IMP:Idle Insert/Remove, rescramble] <-> FEMP/FEDP[Idel Remove/Insert] <-> xGE Descrambled <-> FlexE-Client
ODUflex(B100) <-> MAPOTN [BMP:Nominal] <-> FEMP/FEDP[PCS_VAR] <-> MAC_VAR <-> ENET <-> COPIPIF
